                <note>Carter G. Woodson was a professor and historian at Howard University. He was among the first black scholars to receive a doctoral degree and a pioneer of black history and African American studies. He founded <hi rend="italic">The Journal of African American History</hi> (formally the <hi rend="italic">Journal of Negro History</hi>), was founded in January 1916, as one of the first scholarly texts or journals to cover African-American history. Woodson was the editor until 1950 (Korey Bowers Brown, “Carter G. Woodson,” <hi rend="italic">Our History</hi> Association for the Study of African American Life and History, https://asalh.org/about-us/our-history/). 
                </note>
            </person>
